<mxCell id="c52" value="Scoring definitions (illustrative):&lt;br&gt;Current pain: High = frequent operational problems or high manual effort today; Medium = occasional problems or moderate effort; Low = mostly stable.&lt;br&gt;Strategic importance: High = strongly linked to strategy or differentiation; Medium = supports strategy indirectly; Low = limited strategic influence.&lt;br&gt;Delivery risk: High = complex change with legacy or governance dependencies; Medium = moderate complexity; Low = well understood, low dependency." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#666666;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="20" y="528" width="700" height="118" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
<mxCell id="c53" value="Legend: rating shown as text (High, Medium, Low) and shading; darker shading = higher rating. Colour supports the text; meaning is readable in greyscale. No composite score is calculated. Dimensions are kept separate.&lt;br&gt;Assessment date: 2026-07-02. Owner: illustrative Horizon Bank architecture workshop group. Version: 1.0.&lt;br&gt;The values are illustrative teaching figures, not a factual assessment of a real bank. Capability names: examples/horizon-bank/capabilities.md." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF8DC;strokeColor=#8A6D3B;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="20" y="656" width="700" height="92" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
